issue.title: Get all service principals and applications (paging)
issue.body:
The application and service principal endpoints may only return a limited result set, indicated by the presence of `@odata.nextLink`.
azbrowse should automatically follow these nextLinks until all results are available.

Thanks for building this great tool!

## References
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/paging

comment.body:
Thanks, glad you like it. 

We probably can't iterate all items in one shot as we'd fail with large list sizes, for example an AD tenant with 1000's of service principals in it. 

@stuartleeks worked on paging in the `StorageBlob` provider, it handles this by adding a `next` item to the bottom of the list which will load the following page. 

https://github.com/lawrencegripper/azbrowse/blob/09058b563769277b51856eade59056330f04794d/internal/pkg/expanders/storageBlob.go#L485

Would be interesting to see if we can make this generic over a larger number of providers.

One option, which is currently available and may suit your use case, is to define a custom Resource Graph query which returns the items which are specifically useful to you: https://github.com/lawrencegripper/azbrowse/blob/main/docs/azure-resource-graph.md as a workaround.

https://github.com/lawrencegripper/azbrowse/blob/09058b563769277b51856eade59056330f04794d/internal/pkg/expanders/storageBlob.go#L485

Would be interesting to see if we can make this generic over a larger number of providers.

One option, which is currently available and may suit your use case, is to define a custom Resource Graph query which returns the items which are specifically useful to you: https://github.com/lawrencegripper/azbrowse/blob/main/docs/azure-resource-graph.md as a workaround.
